04/02/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski met with the president of the Macedonian Association of Trade Unions, Vanco Muratovski, Thursday (3 February) to discuss the government's social and economic agenda. Afterwards, Muratovski stressed that 90 per cent of the issues have been harmonised, saying he is hopeful the government will fulfil its commitment to the unions. He added that he had discussed the upcoming structural changes related to eventual EU membership, as well as the arrangements with the IMF and the World Bank. (Utrinski Vesnik - 04/02/05; MIA - 03/02/05)
